# =============================================================================
# Trivy Ignore List — Accepted CVE Risks
# https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#trivyignore
#
# These CVEs are from transitive dependencies of upstream applications
# (e.g., SABnzbd's pip requirements) and cannot be fixed without breaking
# compatibility. They are reviewed monthly and removed once upstream updates.
#
# The nightly security-scan.yml workflow reports ALL vulnerabilities
# regardless of this file.
#
# Last reviewed: 2026-04-02
# =============================================================================

# --- Sonarr / Radarr .NET transitive dependencies ---

# System.Text.Json 6.0.9 → fix in 6.0.10/8.0.5 (bundled by Sonarr upstream)
# DoS in JSON parser — low risk, only processes internal API payloads
CVE-2024-43485

# MimeKit (bundled by Sonarr/Radarr upstream)
# CRLF Injection in Quoted Local-Part — low risk, images do not send email
CVE-2026-30227

# Microsoft.Bcl.Memory (bundled by Sonarr upstream via .NET runtime)
# DoS via memory allocation — low risk, internal API payloads only
CVE-2026-26127

# Microsoft.AspNetCore (bundled by Sonarr upstream via .NET runtime)
# DoS vulnerability — low risk, not internet-facing without reverse proxy
CVE-2026-26130

# Microsoft.IdentityModel.JsonWebTokens 6.8.0 → fix in 6.34.0 (bundled by Sonarr upstream)
# .NET Identity DoS — medium risk, internal API only, no external JWT validation
CVE-2024-21319

# --- SABnzbd Python transitive dependencies ---

# PyJWT 2.10.1 → fix in 2.12.0 (installed by sabnzbd requirements.txt)
# Accepts unknown crit header extensions — low risk in container context
CVE-2026-32597

# orjson 3.11.3 → fix in 3.11.6 (installed by sabnzbd requirements.txt)
# DoS via unbounded recursion — low risk, only processes trusted NZB payloads
CVE-2025-67221

# ujson 5.11.0 → fix in 5.12.0 (installed by sabnzbd requirements.txt)
# DoS via memory leak + large indent — low risk, internal JSON processing only
CVE-2026-32874
CVE-2026-32875

# urllib3 2.5.0 → fix in 2.6.0 (installed by sabnzbd requirements.txt)
# Unbounded decompression chain + streaming API issue — medium risk, mitigated by tini+healthcheck
CVE-2025-66418
CVE-2025-66471

# urllib3 2.5.0 → fix in 2.6.3 (installed by sabnzbd requirements.txt)
# Decompression-bomb safeguard bypass — medium risk, internal downloads only
CVE-2026-21441

# cryptography 46.0.3 → fix in 46.0.5 (installed by sabnzbd requirements.txt)
# Subgroup attack due to missing validation — medium risk, used for HTTPS downloads only,
# not processing untrusted cryptographic input; upgrade attempted via --force-reinstall
# but GHA layer cache may serve stale version until cache expires
# Review: 2026-05-01
CVE-2026-26007

# --- Dashy Node.js transitive dependencies ---
# These are upstream Dashy application dependencies pinned by yarn.lock.
# Fixes require MAJOR version bumps (glob 10→11, minimatch 9→10, tar 6→7)
# that would break the application build. Dashy runs behind a reverse proxy
# in a trusted home network; these deps process only local dashboard config.
# Review: 2026-05-01

# cross-spawn 7.0.3 → fix in 7.0.5 (Dashy transitive dep)
# ReDoS via malicious command arguments — low risk, no user-supplied command execution
CVE-2024-21538

# glob 10.4.2 → fix in 11.1.0 (Dashy transitive dep, MAJOR bump required)
# Command injection via malicious patterns — low risk, only processes local config
CVE-2025-64756

# lodash 4.17.23 → fix in 4.18.0 (Dashy transitive dep)
# Incomplete prototype pollution fix — low risk, dashboard processes trusted config only
CVE-2026-4800

# minimatch 9.0.5 → fix in 10.2.1+ (Dashy transitive dep, MAJOR bump required)
# ReDoS via crafted patterns — low risk, patterns come from local config only
CVE-2026-26996
CVE-2026-27903
CVE-2026-27904

# tar 6.2.1 → fix in 7.5.3+ (Dashy transitive dep, MAJOR bump required)
# Arbitrary file overwrite/creation/read via path traversal — low risk, Dashy
# does not extract user-supplied archives; tar is a build-time transitive dep
CVE-2026-23745
CVE-2026-23950
CVE-2026-24842
CVE-2026-26960
CVE-2026-29786
CVE-2026-31802
